---
// src/pages/credentials/bbb-accredited.astro
// BBB credential page — E-E-A-T signal
// Angle: BBB is the only credential publicly verifiable in real-time + what accreditation actually means
// GSC: 2-3 impressions for "bbb accredited appliance repair" — zero traffic driver, pure trust signal

import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "BBB Accredited — Same Day Appliance Repair LA";
const description = "Same-day repair holds BBB Accreditation. Complaint history publicly viewable at bbb.org. Los Angeles appliance repair.";
const phone = "(424) 325-0520";
const phoneRaw = "4243250520";
const bbbUrl = "https://www.bbb.org/us/ca/los-angeles/profile/appliance-repair/same-day-appliance-repair-1216-1000033588";
const schemaJsons = [
  `{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "LocalBusiness",
  "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair",
  "telephone": "(424) 325-0520",
  "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/credentials/bbb-accredited-appliance-repair/"

  }`,
  `{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does BBB accreditation mean for a home service company?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "BBB Accreditation means the business has applied to the BBB, agreed to uphold the BBB Standards for Trust (honesty in advertising, transparent business practices, responsiveness to complaints), and been accepted based on a review of their business history and practices. It's not automatic — businesses apply, pay an accreditation fee, and are reviewed. Accreditation can be revoked if a business fails to meet the standards. The most important feature of BBB Accreditation for consumers is that the complaint history is publicly visible: anyone can see whether complaints were filed, how they were handled, and whether they were resolved."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does BBB Accreditation actually mean?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "BBB Accreditation is a voluntary program indicating a business meets BBB's published Standards for Trust. Accredited businesses commit to honesty in advertising, transparent business practices, prompt response to customer complaints, and good-faith resolution of disputes. The accreditation status reflects ongoing business behavior — BBB monitors continuously and can revoke accreditation if a business develops a pattern of unresolved complaints. Verify our current accreditation status at bbb.org."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How can I verify Same Day Appliance Repair's BBB accreditation?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "You can verify directly at bbb.org by searching for 'Same Day Appliance Repair Los Angeles' or visiting our BBB profile. The profile shows our accreditation status, current rating, years in business, any complaint history, and customer reviews. This is live information — if our accreditation status or rating changed, it would show there before it changed anywhere on our website."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What happens when a customer files a BBB complaint?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "When a customer files a complaint with the BBB, the BBB forwards it to the business and gives them 14 days to respond. If the business doesn't respond, it affects their rating. If the complaint is resolved, that resolution is documented on the profile. If the business disputes the complaint, the BBB reviews both sides. The key feature: all of this — whether complaints exist, how they were handled, whether they were resolved — is publicly visible on the business's BBB profile indefinitely."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is BBB accreditation the same as a government license?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "No. BBB is a private nonprofit organization, not a government agency. BBB Accreditation is a voluntary program indicating the business meets BBB's standards for trust. It's separate from state licensing requirements. In California, appliance repair companies are regulated by the BHGS (Bureau of Household Goods and Services) under the California DCA. Our BHGS registration number is A49573, which is a state requirement — BBB accreditation is an additional voluntary credential on top of that."
      }
    }
  ]
}`
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((s) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={s}></script>
    ))}
  </Fragment>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; --bbb-blue: #003da5; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 80px 24px 64px; text-align: center; }
  .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero-eyebrow { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 5px 14px; border-radius: 3px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 1.1rem; color: #ccc; max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto 32px; line-height: 1.6; }
  .cta-row { display: flex; gap: 14px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 16px 34px; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; }
  .btn-secondary { background: transparent; color: #fff; padding: 16px 34px; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; border: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.35); }
  .btn-bbb { background: var(--bbb-blue); color: #fff; padding: 16px 34px; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; }
  .hero-meta { margin-top: 28px; color: #aaa; font-size: 0.9rem; display: flex; gap: 24px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 18px 24px; }
  .trust-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px 32px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .container { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-number { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  h2.section-title { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.1rem); font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 16px; line-height: 1.2; }
  .section-black h2.section-title { color: #fff; }
  .intro-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .intro-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .intro-body p { margin: 0 0 18px; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text); }
  /* Sticky CTA */
  .sticky-cta { position: sticky; top: 24px; background: var(--black); border-radius: 10px; padding: 28px 24px; color: #fff; text-align: center; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-label { font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-phone { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; display: block; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .sticky-cta .btn-cta { display: block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px; border-radius: 5px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .sticky-cta .btn-cta-bbb { display: block; background: var(--bbb-blue); color: #fff; padding: 14px; border-radius: 5px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-sub { font-size: 0.82rem; color: #888; }
  .cta-divider { border: none; border-top: 1px solid #222; margin: 18px 0; }
  .cta-detail { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .cta-detail li { margin-bottom: 6px; padding-left: 18px; position: relative; font-size: 0.85rem; color: #aaa; }
  .cta-detail li::before { content: "✓"; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--red); font-weight: 700; }
  /* Rating display */
  .rating-block { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; padding: 28px; margin-top: 28px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr; gap: 28px; align-items: center; }
  @media (max-width: 600px) { .rating-block { grid-template-columns: 1fr; text-align: center; } }
  .rating-letter { font-size: 5rem; font-weight: 900; color: var(--bbb-blue); line-height: 1; }
  .rating-plus { font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 900; color: var(--bbb-blue); vertical-align: super; }
  .rating-label { font-size: 0.8rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 4px; }
  .rating-body h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 8px; }
  .rating-body p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .verify-link { display: inline-block; background: var(--bbb-blue); color: #fff; padding: 10px 20px; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; }
  /* What BBB checks */
  .check-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; margin-top: 28px; }
  .check-card { background: #111; border: 1px solid #1a1a1a; border-radius: 8px; padding: 20px 18px; }
  .check-card.key { border-color: rgba(0,61,165,0.3); }
  .check-icon { font-size: 1.4rem; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .check-card h3 { font-size: 0.92rem; font-weight: 700; color: #fff; margin: 0 0 8px; }
  .check-card p { font-size: 0.84rem; color: #c0c0c0; line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }
  /* Standards list */
  .standards-list { margin-top: 28px; }
  .standard-item { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 18px 20px; margin-bottom: 12px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 32px 1fr; gap: 14px; align-items: start; }
  .std-num { width: 32px; height: 32px; background: var(--bbb-blue); color: #fff; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.82rem; font-weight: 800; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .std-body h3 { font-size: 0.92rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 4px; color: var(--text); }
  .std-body p { font-size: 0.86rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }
  /* Verifiable in real time callout */
  .verify-block { background: #0a1a3a; border: 1px solid rgba(0,61,165,0.4); border-radius: 10px; padding: 26px 24px; margin-top: 28px; }
  .verify-block .v-label { font-size: 0.73rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: #5080d0; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .verify-block h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; margin: 0 0 10px; }
  .verify-block p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: #c0d0e8; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 16px; }
  .verify-block a { display: inline-block; background: var(--bbb-blue); color: #fff; padding: 11px 22px; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; }
  /* Credentials nav */
  .creds-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(190px, 1fr)); gap: 14px; margin-top: 28px; }
  .cred-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 18px 16px; text-decoration: none; display: block; }
  .cred-card:hover { border-color: var(--red); }
  .cred-card .cred-icon { font-size: 1.4rem; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .cred-card h3 { font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); margin: 0 0 4px; }
  .cred-card p { font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--muted); margin: 0; line-height: 1.4; }
  /* FAQ */
  .faq-list { margin-top: 36px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-item:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .faq-item h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); margin: 0 0 10px; }
  .faq-item p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
  .nearby-links { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px; margin-top: 24px; }
  .nearby-links a { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 4px; padding: 8px 16px; font-size: 0.87rem; color: var(--text); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; }
  .nearby-links a:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 64px 24px; text-align: center; }
  .bottom-cta h2 { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 16px; }
  .bottom-cta p { color: #aaa; margin: 0 0 32px; font-size: 1.05rem; }
</style>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-eyebrow">BBB Accredited Business · Publicly Verifiable</div>
  <h1>BBB Accredited — The One Credential You Can Verify in Real Time</h1>
  <p class="hero-sub">Our BBB profile is live and public. Complaint history, rating, accreditation status — all visible at bbb.org right now, not just on our website. That's what makes it different from every other credential we carry.</p>
  <div class="cta-row">
    <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
    <a href={bbbUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-bbb">View BBB Profile ↗</a>
    <a href="/book" class="btn-secondary">Schedule Service</a>
  </div>
  <div class="hero-meta">
    <span>⭐ BBB Accredited Business</span>
    <span>📋 BHGS Registered #A49573</span>
    <span>🛡 Fully Insured</span>
    <span>🔬 EPA-608 Certified</span>
    <span>✅ Background Checked</span>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TRUST BAR -->
<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-inner">
    <span class="trust-item">⭐ BBB Accredited Business</span>
    <span class="trust-item">🛠 90-Day Warranty</span>
    <span class="trust-item">📋 BHGS #A49573</span>
    <span class="trust-item">🛡 General Liability + Workers Comp</span>
    <span class="trust-item">🔬 EPA-608 Universal</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-body">
        <p class="section-number">01 — What Makes BBB Different</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Every other credential has to be taken on faith. BBB is public record.</h2>

        <p>Our BHGS registration can be verified at bhgs.dca.ca.gov. Our EPA-608 certification is a tested credential. Our insurance can be confirmed with a Certificate of Insurance. But none of those show you our complaint history. BBB does.</p>

        <p>The BBB profile for Same Day Appliance Repair is publicly visible at bbb.org right now. If a customer filed a complaint — how it was handled, whether it was resolved, whether we responded at all — that's there. Our accreditation status reflects that history: responsive handling of any issues that came up, no outstanding unresolved disputes, no government actions against the business. The current rating is on the live profile — verify it directly.</p>

        <p>That's the thing about BBB accreditation that makes it worth more than a badge on a website. It's not self-reported. It's not a one-time check. The profile is live, it updates as our business history updates, and anyone can see it before they book.</p>

        <div class="rating-block">
          <div>
            <div class="rating-letter">✓</div>
            <div class="rating-label">BBB Accredited</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rating-body">
            <h3>What BBB Accreditation reflects</h3>
            <p>Clean complaint record, responsive handling of any issues, no outstanding unresolved disputes, no government actions. BBB monitors accredited businesses continuously — current status and rating are visible on the live profile.</p>
            <a href={bbbUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="verify-link">Verify at bbb.org ↗</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="sticky-cta">
        <div class="cta-label">Schedule Service</div>
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="cta-phone">{phone}</a>
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-cta">Call Now</a>
        <a href={bbbUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-cta-bbb">View BBB Profile ↗</a>
        <a href="/book" class="btn-cta" style="background:#222; margin-top:-4px;">Schedule Online</a>
        <div class="cta-sub">Accredited · Publicly verifiable</div>
        <hr class="cta-divider" />
        <ul class="cta-detail">
          <li>BBB Accredited Business</li>
          <li>BHGS Registration #A49573</li>
          <li>Background checked technicians</li>
          <li>$89 diagnostic — waived with repair</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- WHAT BBB CHECKS -->
<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02 — What BBB Accreditation Actually Involves</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">It's not automatic — businesses apply and are reviewed</h2>

    <div class="check-grid">
      <div class="check-card key">
        <div class="check-icon">📋</div>
        <h3>Application and Review</h3>
        <p>BBB Accreditation requires a business to apply, pay an annual accreditation fee, and be reviewed based on their business history. Not every applicant is accepted. Businesses with significant unresolved complaints or government actions won't qualify.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="check-card key">
        <div class="check-icon">📊</div>
        <h3>Public Complaint History</h3>
        <p>Every complaint filed against an accredited business, and how it was handled, is visible on the BBB profile. This is permanent — complaints don't disappear. The record shows whether issues were resolved and whether the business responded at all.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="check-card">
        <div class="check-icon">🔄</div>
        <h3>Ongoing Monitoring</h3>
        <p>Accreditation isn't a one-time review. BBB monitors businesses continuously and can revoke accreditation if a company develops a pattern of unresolved complaints or violates the Standards for Trust. The rating updates based on ongoing behavior.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="check-card">
        <div class="check-icon">⭐</div>
        <h3>Customer Reviews</h3>
        <p>Customer reviews on BBB are verified — BBB confirms the reviewer had a business transaction with the company. Reviews from customers who have no verifiable interaction aren't published. The review total and score are separate from the complaint record.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="check-card">
        <div class="check-icon">📞</div>
        <h3>Complaint Response Requirement</h3>
        <p>When a customer files a BBB complaint, the business has 14 days to respond. Failure to respond damages the rating. BBB tracks response rates and resolution rates as part of the overall rating calculation — so ignoring complaints is not an option.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="check-card">
        <div class="check-icon">⚖️</div>
        <h3>Government Action Check</h3>
        <p>BBB reviews for any government or regulatory actions against the business. Government fines, license revocations, or legal judgments related to business practices affect accreditation eligibility and the rating calculation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- BBB STANDARDS FOR TRUST -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">03 — The BBB Standards for Trust</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What accredited businesses commit to</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--muted); margin:0 0 8px; font-size:0.95rem;">BBB Accreditation requires agreement to eight Standards for Trust. These are the specific commitments our accreditation reflects.</p>

    <div class="standards-list">
      <div class="standard-item">
        <div class="std-num">1</div>
        <div class="std-body">
          <h3>Build Trust</h3>
          <p>Establish and maintain a positive track record in the marketplace through honest business practices and a history of keeping commitments.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="standard-item">
        <div class="std-num">2</div>
        <div class="std-body">
          <h3>Advertise Honestly</h3>
          <p>Adhere to established standards of advertising and selling. No misleading claims, hidden terms, or deceptive pricing in any marketing or communications.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="standard-item">
        <div class="std-num">3</div>
        <div class="std-body">
          <h3>Tell the Truth</h3>
          <p>Honestly represent products and services, including clear disclosure of all material facts that could affect a consumer's decision to buy.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="standard-item">
        <div class="std-num">4</div>
        <div class="std-body">
          <h3>Be Transparent</h3>
          <p>Openly identify the nature, location, and ownership of the business, and clearly disclose all policies and procedures relevant to the consumer relationship.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="standard-item">
        <div class="std-num">5</div>
        <div class="std-body">
          <h3>Honor Promises</h3>
          <p>Abide by all written agreements and verbal representations. If a technician quotes a price over the phone, that's what appears on the invoice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="standard-item">
        <div class="std-num">6</div>
        <div class="std-body">
          <h3>Be Responsive</h3>
          <p>Address marketplace disputes quickly, professionally, and in good faith. Respond to BBB complaints within the required timeframe with substantive answers.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="standard-item">
        <div class="std-num">7</div>
        <div class="std-body">
          <h3>Safeguard Privacy</h3>
          <p>Protect any information collected from customers and only use it in ways they would reasonably expect. No selling or sharing personal data with third parties.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="standard-item">
        <div class="std-num">8</div>
        <div class="std-body">
          <h3>Embody Integrity</h3>
          <p>Approach all business dealings with integrity and good faith. The standard that underpins all others — consistent honesty in every customer interaction.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="verify-block">
      <div class="v-label">🔍 Public Record — Verify Right Now</div>
      <h3>Our full BBB profile, rating, and complaint history are live at bbb.org</h3>
      <p>You don't have to take our word for our accreditation status. The profile updates in real time as our business history changes. If anything were different, it would show there first.</p>
      <a href={bbbUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">View Our BBB Profile ↗</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CREDENTIALS NAV -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">04 — Our Full Credentials</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">BBB alongside a complete verification stack</h2>
    <div class="creds-grid">
      <a href="/credentials/licensed/" class="cred-card">
        <div class="cred-icon">📋</div>
        <h3>BHGS Registered</h3>
        <p>California #A49573 — verifiable at bhgs.dca.ca.gov</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/credentials/epa-certified/" class="cred-card">
        <div class="cred-icon">🔬</div>
        <h3>EPA-608 Universal</h3>
        <p>Federal refrigerant handling certification.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/credentials/insured/" class="cred-card">
        <div class="cred-icon">🛡</div>
        <h3>Fully Insured</h3>
        <p>GL, Workers Comp, Commercial Auto. COI on request.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/credentials/background-checked/" class="cred-card">
        <div class="cred-icon">✅</div>
        <h3>Background Checked</h3>
        <p>Criminal, sex offender registry, identity verified.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/credentials/bbb-accredited/" class="cred-card" style="border-color:var(--bbb-blue);">
        <div class="cred-icon">⭐</div>
        <h3>BBB Accredited Business</h3>
        <p>Publicly verifiable at bbb.org. You are here.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/credentials/osha-certified/" class="cred-card">
        <div class="cred-icon">⚠️</div>
        <h3>OSHA Safety Trained</h3>
        <p>Gas, electrical, ergonomic, chemical hazard protocols.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">05 — Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">BBB Accreditation — what homeowners ask</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What does BBB accreditation mean for a home service company?</h3>
        <p>It means the business applied, was reviewed, and agreed to uphold BBB Standards for Trust — including honest advertising, transparent practices, and responsive complaint handling. Most importantly, the complaint history is publicly visible on the profile: anyone can see whether complaints were filed and how they were handled.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What does BBB Accreditation actually mean?</h3>
        <p>BBB Accreditation is a voluntary program indicating a business meets BBB's published Standards for Trust. Accredited businesses commit to honesty in advertising, transparent business practices, prompt response to customer complaints, and good-faith resolution of disputes. The accreditation status reflects ongoing business behavior — BBB monitors continuously and can revoke accreditation if a business develops a pattern of unresolved complaints.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How can I verify the BBB accreditation and rating?</h3>
        <p>Directly at bbb.org — search "Same Day Appliance Repair Los Angeles" or use the link on this page. The profile shows accreditation status, rating, years in business, any complaint history, and customer reviews. It's live information, not a screenshot.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What happens when a customer files a BBB complaint?</h3>
        <p>BBB forwards the complaint to the business and requires a response within 14 days. No response damages the rating. Resolution and handling are documented on the profile permanently. All of this is publicly visible.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Is BBB accreditation the same as a government license?</h3>
        <p>No. BBB is a private nonprofit, not a government agency. Our state requirement is BHGS registration #A49573 under the California DCA. BBB Accreditation is an additional voluntary credential on top of that — they serve different purposes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

